    "Otherwise, if they are provided with accurate and comprehensive explanatory information, they will tend to feel fairer about the results, regardless of whether the evaluator is an AI or a teacher.",
    "This study aims to investigate the impact of evaluator type (teachers vs. AI algorithms) on students' perceptions of fairness in higher education evaluation, as well as the role of information transparency and interpretation in this process.",
    "The research questions are: Do college students perceive a higher level of fairness when an AI algorithm is used as the evaluator compared to traditional teacher evaluation?",
    "How does the use of an AI algorithm affect the fairness perception of college students?",
    "What are the boundary conditions for this influence on fairness perception?"
